%N A011006 Decimal expansion of 4th root of 8.
%H A011006 Vincenzo Librandi, <a href="/A011006/b011006.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..5000</a>
%H A011006 Amrik Singh Nimbran, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13226-016-0193-4">Extending Euler's product for sqrt(2)</a>, Indian Journal of Pure and Applied Mathematics, Vol. 47, No. 4 (2016), pp. 697-703.
%H A011006 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A011006 Equals 2*A228497 = 2^(3/4) = sqrt(A010466). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 15 2021
%F A011006 From _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 02 2026: (Start)
%F A011006 Equals Product_{k>=1} (8*k-6)*(8*k-4)/((8*k-7)*(8*k-3)) (Nimbran, 2016, p. 700, eq. (21)).
%F A011006 Equals Product_{k>=1} (8*k-1)*(8*k+3)/((8*k-4)*(8*k+6)) (Nimbran, 2016, p. 700, eq. (22)).
%F A011006 Equals Product_{k>=1} (8*k-4)^3/((8*k-6)*(8*k-5)*(8*k-1)) (Nimbran, 2016, p. 700, eq. (23)). (End)
